Name: bias
Title: Mean Error
Abstract: Average signed prediction error indicating overestimation or underestimation

Name: count
Title: Count
Abstract: Number of observations in the dataset

Name: cv
Title: Coefficient of Variation
Abstract: Relative measure of dispersion defined as standard deviation divided by the mean

Name: fx
Title: Cumulative Probability
Abstract: The Probability of being not-exceeded F(X) = 1 â€“ P(X)

Name: iqr
Title: Interquartile Range
Abstract: Spread between the 75th and 25th percentiles

Name: mae
Title: Mean Absolute Error
Abstract: Average of absolute prediction errors

Name: max
Title: Maximum
Abstract: Largest observed value

Name: mean
Title: Mean
Abstract: Arithmetic mean of the sample or population values

Name: min
Title: Minimum
Abstract: Smallest observed value

Name: p05
Title: 5th Percentile
Abstract: Value below which 5% of the observations fall

Name: p25
Title: 25th Percentile
Abstract: Value below which 25% of the observations fall

Name: p50
Title: 50th Percentile
Abstract: Value below which 50% of the observations fall

Name: p75
Title: 75th Percentile
Abstract: Value below which 75% of the observations fall

Name: p95
Title: 95th Percentile
Abstract: Value below which 95% of the observations fall

Name: pvalue
Title: P-Value
Abstract: Probability measure used to evaluate statistical significance under a null hypothesis

Name: px
Title: Exceedance Probability
Abstract: Probability of a value being exceeded P(X>=x)

Name: r
Title: Correlation Coefficient
Abstract: Pearson correlation coefficient representing linear association strength

Name: r2
Title: Coefficient of Determination
Abstract: Proportion of variance in the dependent variable explained by the model

Name: range
Title: Range
Abstract: Difference between maximum and minimum

Name: rmse
Title: Root Mean Squared Error
Abstract: Square root of the average of squared prediction errors

Name: sd
Title: Standard Deviation
Abstract: Square root of variance, representing spread in the same units as the data

Name: sum
Title: Sum
Abstract: Total sum of all observed values

Name: tx
Title: Return Period
Abstract: Reciprocal of exceedance probability T(X) = 1/P(X)

Name: variance
Title: Variance
Abstract: Measure of dispersion representing the average squared deviation from the mean
